<plot>In this 'period piece' (Election Day 1968), George Roundy is a Beverly Hills hairstylist who's uncontrolled libido stands between him and his ambitions. He wants the security of a relationship. He wants to be a hairdressing "star" and open his own salon. But the fact that he beds down with the wife, daughter, and mistress of a potential backer doesn't help. It also does little for his relationship with the woman thinks she's his main squeeze. As this tongue-in-cheek look at the sexual revolution rolls on, the babe juggling, stress and lies all wear George down. He wants so much. But a hungry kid loose in a candy store easily gets sick.</plot><url>http://localhost:8983/solr/movie.html?490388</url></doc>
